<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="50" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,977]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,332,881,905]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is combined from Latin prefix 
<emphasis box="[893,932,880,904]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">sub</emphasis>
- and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Watson" authorityYear="1957" box="[997,1093,881,904]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unispina">
<emphasis box="[997,1093,881,904]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">unispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which refers to the close relationship between the new species and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Watson" authorityYear="1957" box="[578,702,917,940]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unispina">
<emphasis box="[578,702,917,940]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">T. unispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
